-- Sub-Saharan Africa Stocks: Sasini Gains, Omnicane Rises
-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n   a n d   J a n a   M a r a i s
-- 2012-03-30T15:42:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-30/sub-saharan-africa-stocks-mumias-sugar-gains-omnicane-rises.html
The  Nigerian Stock Exchange All-
Share Index (NGSEINDX)  declined for a sixth day, and closed 0.5 percent
down at 20,652.47 in Lagos, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg.  The  FTSE/Namibia Overall Index (FTN098)  gained for the first time in
three days, rising 0.6 to 887.72 by the close in Windhoek, the
capital. Kenya’s  All-Share Index (NSEASI)  advanced 0.1 percent to 59.81
in Nairobi. Mauritius’s  SEMDEX Index (SEMDEX)  gained for a ninth day, its
longest winning streak in a year, adding 0.7 percent to 1,806.05
by the close in Port Louis.  The following shares were active in sub-Saharan Africa,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Omnicane Ltd. (MTMD)  , a Mauritian sugar producer with
interests in energy, closed at the highest in more than 10
weeks, jumping 1.4 percent to 73 rupees. Net income climbed to
392.9 million rupees ($13.5 million) in the 12 months through
December, from 248.9 million rupees a year earlier, the Port
Louis-based company said in a statement on the Stock Exchange of
Mauritius’s website today.  Sasini Ltd. (STCL)  , a Kenyan tea and coffee grower,
climbed 2.8 percent to 11.05 shillings. The Tea Board of Kenya
said it plans to increase shipments of processed and packaged
tea to boost foreign-exchange earnings. The bulk of Kenya’s tea
produce is currently sold in bulk.  Editors: Peter Branton, Ana Monteiro  To contact the reporters on this story:
